| 17th| +6 | —                                                                 | 7 || 5th || 4 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 2 |
| 18th| +6 | Elemental Shield (4/rest)                                         | 8 || 5th || 4 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 2 |
| 19th| +6 | Ability Score Improvement                                         | 8 || 5th || 4 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 2 |
| 20th| +6 | Ascendance                                                        | 8 || 5th || 4 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 2 |
</div>

### Creating a Shaman
When creating an elemental shaman, consider how the elements affect your personality. Although elemental shaman have resonance with all four primary elements, some tend to outwardly display aspects of one over the others. Those leaning towards fire might be impatient, temperamental, or full of energy in everything they do. Water leaning shaman are adaptable, chaotic, and tend to go with the flow. Those who favor earth are typically lawful, stalwart, and stubborn. Shaman who favor air are aloof, distant, and typically the most neutral in arbitrations. 

Think about your bond with your totems and how they represent the elemental planes from which you gain your power. Are they simply tools to you for channelling raw planar power, or are they sacred and worthy of reverence? Do they act as representations of a favored element or do you use them to keep a favored element in check? How a shaman perceives their connection to the elemental planes should be reflected in the totems they summon forth.

#### Quick Build
You can make a shaman quickly by following these suggestions. First, Wisdom should be your highest ability score, followed by Constitution. If you intend to engage in melee combat regularly, make Strength your second highest ability score instead.

\columnbreak

## Class Features
As a shaman, you gain the following class features.

#### Hit Points
___
- **Hit Dice:** 1d8 per shaman level
- **Hit Points at 1st Level:** 8 + your Constitution modifier
- **Hit Points at Higher Levels:** 1d8 + your Constitution modifier per shaman level after 1st

#### Proficiencies
___
- **Armor:** Light armor, medium armor, shields
- **Weapons:** Simple weapons, martial weapons
- **Tools:** Herbalism kit
___
- **Saving Throws:** Strength, Wisdom
- **Skills:** Choose two from Animal handling, Arcana, History, Insight, Medicine, Nature, Perception, and Survival

#### Equipment
You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:
 - *(a)* scale mail or *(b)* studded leather
 - *(a)* a mace and shield or *(b)* two martial weapons
 - *(a)* a dungeoneer's pack or *(b)* an explorer's pack
 - a druidic focus

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/cPPYV7h.png' style='position:absolute; top:0px; right:0px; width:1200px' />

\pagebreakNum

### Spellcasting
As a link between the elements. you can cast shaman spells. See chapter 10 of the Player's Handbook for the general rules of spellcasting and chapter 6 of this book for the shaman spell list.

#### Cantrips
At 1st level, you know three cantrips of your choice from the shaman spell list. You learn additional shaman cantrips of your choice at higher levels, as shown in the Cantrips Known column of the Shaman table.

#### Preparing and Casting Spells
The Shaman table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level and higher. To cast one of these spells, you must expend a slot of the spell's level or higher. You regain expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.

You prepare the list of shaman spells that are available for you to cast, choosing from the shaman spell list. When you do so, choose a number of shaman spells equal to your Wisdom modifier + your shaman level (minimum of 1 spell) The spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots.

For example, if you are a 4th-level shaman, you have four 1st-level and two 2nd-level spell slots. With a Wisdom of 16, your list of prepared spells can include seven spells of 1st or 2nd level, in any combination. If you prepare the 1st-level spell *absorb element*, you can cast it using a 1st-level or 2nd-level slot. Casting the spell doesn't remove it from your list of prepared spells.

You can change your list of prepared spells when you finish a long rest. Preparing a new list of shaman spells requires time spent communing with the elements: at least 1 minute per spell level for each spell on your list.

#### Spellcasting Ability
Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your shaman spells. The power of your spells comes from the elements and spirits. You use your Wisdom whenever a shaman spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a shaman spell and when making an attack roll with one.

<div style="text-align: Center">

**Spell save DC** = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

**Spell attack modifier** = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier
</div>

#### Spellcasting Focus
You can use a druidic focus as a spellcasting focus for your shaman spells.

### Totemist
You can bind elemental forces into helpful totems to aid you and your allies, or rain havoc upon your foes. See the end of the class description for the shaman totem list.

#### Summoning Totems
You have a number of totem slots equal to your Totems Known + your Wisdom modifier. To summon one of your totems, you must expend a totem slot. You regain expended totem slots when you finish a long rest.

You can use your action to summon a totem, placing it in an unoccupied square within 30 feet of you. Each totem fills an element when summoned, you can only have one totem of each element active, for a maximum of four totems at once.

#### Totems Known at 1st Level and Higher
You know two totems of your choice. Your totem options are detailed at the end of the class description. When you gain certain shaman levels, you learn to bind additional totems of your choice, as shown in the Totems Known column of the Shaman table.

Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the totems you know and replace it with another totem that you could have learnt at that level.

#### Totems Level and Abilities
The Shaman table shows what the level of your totems cast spell is; all of your totems spells are the same level. 

When you summon a totem, it immediately casts its spell, all its effects controlled by you. A summoned totem lasts for up to 1 minute, unless otherwise specified, and can be dismissed as a free action.

Your summoned totems have an AC of 11 + your Wisdom modifier, hit points equal to twice your shaman level and immunity to poison and psychic damage.

### Fighting Style
At 2nd level, you adopt a style of fighting as your specialty. Choose one of the following options. You can't take a Fight-ing Style option more than once, even if you later get to choose again.

#### Defense
While you are wearing armor, you gain a +1 bonus to AC.

#### Dueling
When you are wielding a melee weapon in one hand and no other weapons, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with that weapon.

#### Great Weapon Fighting
When you roll a 1 or 2 on a damage die for an attack you make with a melee weapon that you are wielding with two hands, you can reroll the die and must use the new roll, even if the new roll is a 1 or 2. The weapon must have the two-handed or versatile property for you to use this benefit.

#### Two-Weapon Fighting
When you engage in two-weapon fighting, you can add your ability modifier to the damage of the second attack.

### Shamanistic Binding
When you reach 3rd level, you enter a shamanistic binding, deepening your understanding of elements in a certain aspect. Choose Elemental, Enhancement, or Restoration, each of which is detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level, and again at 7th, 11th, and 15th level.

#### Binding Spells
Each binding has a list of spells that you gain at the sha-man levels noted in the binding description. Once you gain a binding spell, it is always prepared, and it doesn't count against the number of spells you can prepare each day

If you gain a binding spell that does not appear on the shaman spell list, the spells is a shaman spell for you.

### Elemental Shield
At 3rd level, you gain the ability to manifest elements into beneficial shields. You gain two such shields: Water Shield and a shield determined by your binding.

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/cPPYV7h.png' style='position:absolute; top:0px; right:0px; width:1200px' />

\pagebreakNum

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When you use your Elemental Shield, you choose which shield to manifest. You must then finish a short or long rest to use your Elemental shield again.

An elemental shield lasts for 1 hour, or until all uses of its active effect have been expended.

At 6th, 13th, and 18th level you gain an additional use of your Elemental Shield between rests, regaining expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.

#### Water Shield
As an action, you manifest a number of water orbs equal to your Wisdom modifier. The orbs hover around you for their duration before falling to the ground.

Whenever you roll damage for an attack or a spell cast using a spell slot, you can expend an orb to reroll any number of dice, and use either dice roll.

### Ability Score Improvement
When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.

### Spirit Animal
Starting at 5th level, you can use your bonus action to magically assume the shape of your spirit animal. You can use this feature twice. You regain expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.

While shapeshifted in this way, your AC is 14, and you gain a movement speed of 50 feet, the rest of your game statistics remain unchanged.

You can stay as your spirit animal for 1 hour. You then revert back to your normal form unless you expend another use of this feature. You can revert to your normal form earlier by using a bonus action on your turn. You automatically revert if you fall unconscious, drop to 0 hit points, die, or make an attack or cast a spell that affects an enemy creature.

*A deeper explanation of a shaman's spirit animal can be found in Appendix A at the end of this book.*

### Astral Shift
Beginning at 9th level, as reaction upon taking damage to shift your body into the astral plane, giving you resistance towards all damage until the start of your next turn.

You can use this feature twice, regaining expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.

### Totemist Projection
Upon reaching 10th level, you are able to summon a totem of each element using a bonus action, placing each totem in an unoccupied square within 30 feet of you.

In addition, you can use your bonus action to move any active totems to a new location within 30 feet of you.

### Bloodlust
Starting at 14th level, as an action, you can insight a blood-lust within you and allies within 30 feet of yourself that lasts for 1 minute, or until you lose your concentration (as if you were concentrating on a spell). Each affected ally gains the benefits of a *haste* spell, and adds your Wisdom modi-fier to attack and damage rolls for the duration.

Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.

\columnbreak

### Ascendance
At 20th level, you can draw greater empowerment from the elements. As a bonus action, your body fills with elemental energy, shifting your form to an ascendant. Ascendance lasts for 1 minute, giving you the benefit of your Binding.

Once you have used this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.

#### Elemental
You become empowered by fire, immediately after you cast a spell using a spell slot, you can use your bonus action to cast a second spell with a casting time of an action.

#### Enhancement
You become empowered by wind, you add your Wisdom modifier to attack and damage rolls made with melee weapons, the extra damage is dealt as lightning damage.

#### Restoration
You become empowered by water, making your chain heal-ing able to affect any number of creatures within range, instead of just one.

## Shamanistic Binding
Shamans strive to deepen their understanding and connec-tion with the elements no matter what. Some shamans prefer a more brutal approach to shamanism, either in the shape of strict melee combat, or conjuring raw element powers against their enemies. Others still, stand as the conjurers of healing waters and restorative energies.

### Elemental
Elemental shamans have dedicated themselves above all else to forging a deep bond with the elements. Making them able to channel such power into destructive magical surges. They manipulate the land itself. To battle an elemental shaman is to taunt the very forces of nature.

##### Elemental Binding Spells
| Shaman Level|&nbsp;| Spells         |
|:----:|:-|:--------------------------|
| 3rd  || earth tremor, witch bolt    |
| 4th  || dragon's breath, earthbind  |
| 7th  || call lightning, tidal wave  |
| 10th || control water, storm sphere |
| 15th || maelstrom, wall of stone    |

#### Destructive Attunement
At 3rd level, whenever you cast a spell that deals cold, fire, lightning or thunder damage, before determining damage you may choose to change the damage type to one of the damage types on the list above.

#### Lightning Shield
Starting at 7th level, as an action, you manifest a lightning orb with a number of charges equal to your Wisdom modifier. Whenever you hit a creature with a spell, you can expend a charge of your orb to make deal an additional 2d4 lightning damage to a creature hit by your spell.

Additionally, you can use your reaction when hit by a melee attack to expend a charge and deal 2d4 lightning damage to the attacker.

Lightning shields damage increases by 1d4 when you reach 11th level (3d4), and 17th level (4d4).

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/cPPYV7h.png' style='position:absolute; top:0px; right:0px; width:1200px' />

\pagebreakNum

#### Resonance
Upon reaching 11th level, when you cast a spell that deals cold, fire, lightning or thunder damage using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you regain one expended spell slot. The slot you regain must be of a level lower than the spell you cast and can't be higher than 5th level.

You can recover spell slots with a combined level equal to half your shaman level. Resetting the pool of spell slots that can be regained when you finish a long rest.

#### Improved Lightning Shield
At 15th level, when you use your Lightning Shield, you manifest an additional orb with charges equal to your Wis-dom modifier. When you hit a creature with a spell, or are hit by a melee attack, you may choose to have both orbs lash out against the target, instead of just one.

In addition, a creature hit by your orb must succeed a Constitution saving throw, or be unable to use its reaction until the beginning of your next turn.

### Enhancement
Enhancement shamans are in as intense communion with the elements as the elemental shaman. What differentiates them is their combat methodology. They favor empowering their physical attacks with elemental energies and facing their adversaries up close.

##### Enhancement Binding Spells
| Shaman Level|&nbsp;| Spells            |
|:----:|:-|:-----------------------------|
| 3rd  || absorb elements, searing smite |
| 4th  || flame blade, warding wind      |
| 7th  || elemental weapon, haste        |
| 10th || fire shield, stoneskin         |
| 15th || far step, hold monster         |

#### Imbue Weapon
At 3rd level, you can imbue your weapons with raw elemen-tal energy. As a bonus action, choose a weapon that you are holding. That weapon becomes imbued for 1 hour, or until you use a bonus action to remove the imbuement. You can only have two weapons imbued at a time.

***Flametongue.*** You imbue your weapon with elemental flames, causing it to emit dim light in a 10-feet radius.

Additionally, when you hit a creature with this weapon you may expend a 1st-level spell slot to deal an additional 2d6 fire damage. This damage increases by 1d6 for each spell slot level above 1st.

***Frostbrand.*** You imbue your weapon with elemental ice, giving the wielder resistance to extreme heat.

Additionally, when you hit a creature with this weapon you may expend a 1st-level spell slot to deal an additional 1d8 cold damage and reduce the targets speed by 5 feet. This damage increases by 1d8 and reduces the targets speed for an extra 5 feet for each spell slot level above 1st.

***Windfury.*** You imbue your weapon with elemental air, doubling the wielders jump distance.

Additionally, when you hit a creature with this weapon you may expend a 1st-level spell slot to deal an additional 1d6 slashing damage to your target and each creature within 5 feet of it. This damage increases by 1d6 for each spell slot level above 1st.

\columnbreak

#### Wind Shield
Starting at 7th level, as an action, you manifest the air around you. Your movement speed increases by 10 feet, climbing does not require additional movement, and you are unaffected by natural difficult terrain.

Additionally, you can attack twice, instead of once, when-ever you take the Attack action on your turn.

#### Stormstrikes
Upon reaching 11th level, your weapon attacks counts as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.

In addition, once per turn, you can deal an extra 1d10 lightning damage to one creature you hit with an attack.

#### Spirit Wolves
At 15th level, as an action you are able to call forth two spirit wolves to aid you. The wolves act on your initiative, obeying your commands as best they can. If no commands are given they use their action to attack the nearest enemy, being intelligent enough to tell friend from foe. 

The wolves lasts for 1 minute, or until killed. Once used, you can't use this feature again until you finish a long rest. A statblock for these wolves can be found in Appendix A.

### Restoration
Restoration shamans find a deep connection with water, using it soothing powers to restore life and heal afflictions. They finding harmony in the nature and purifying their allies as a tidal surge washes across a sandy shore.

##### Restoration Binding Spells
| Shaman Level|&nbsp;| Spells              |
|:----:|:-|:-------------------------------|
| 3rd  || bless, cure wounds               |
| 4th  || aid, lesser restoration          |
| 7th  || remove curse, revivify           |
| 10th || death ward, guardian of faith    |
| 15th || greater restoration, reincarnate |

#### Earth Shield
At 3rd level, as a bonus action, you manifest a number of earthen orbs equal to your Wisdom modifier around a creature within 30 feet of you. Whenever the affected creature is hit by an attack that you can see, you can use your reaction to reduce the damage dealt by an amount equal to your shaman level.

#### Ritual Caster
Also at 3rd level, you can cast a shaman spell as a ritual if that spell has the ritual tag and you have the spell prepared.

#### Resurgence
Starting at 7th level, the healing spells you cast on others heal you as well. When you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that restores hit points to a creature other than you, you regain hit points equal to 2 + the spell's level.

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/cPPYV7h.png' style='position:absolute; top:0px; right:0px; width:1200px' />
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/gbQme1i.png' style='position:absolute; top:850px; right:-200px; width:700px;transform:rotate(190deg)' />

\pagebreakNum

#### Chain Healing
Upon reaching 11th level, whenever you use spell of 1st level or higher to restore hit points to one creature, you can cause the spell to affect a nearby ally as well. As a bonus action, choose a creature within 10 feet of the healed target, that creature is healed for an amount equal to the initial target.

#### Surge of Life
At 15th level, when you use a spell of 1st level or higher to restore hit points, you may choose to restore the maximum amount of hit points possible. Additionally, each creature healed this way gains temporary hit points equal to half your shaman level.

Once used, you can't use this feature again until you finish a long rest.

## Totems
If a totem has prerequisites, you must meet them to learn it. You can learn the totem at the same time that you meet its prerequisites. A level prerequisite in a totem refers to your shaman level, not your character level.

#### Cleansing Totem
*Prerequisite: 5th level, (totem of water)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a cleansing totem, that casts the *lesser restoration* spell on a creature within 30 feet of it. After which the totem dissipates.

#### Cloudburst Totem
*Prerequisite: 17th level, (totem of water)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a cloudburst totem, that casts the *mass cure wounds* spell. Once cast, the totem dissipates.

#### Counterstrike Totem
*Prerequisite: 9th level, (totem of air)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a counterstrike totem, the totem prepares the *counterspell* spell, for the duration of the totem, you can use your reaction to release the totems spell to attempt to counter a spell within 60 feet of it. Once you have released this spell, the totem dissipates.

#### Earthgrab Totem
*(totem of earth)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down an earthgrab totem, that casts the *maxi-milian's earthen grasp* spell, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Earthquake Totem
*(totem of earth)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down an earthquake totem, that casts the *earth tremor* spell around it. On subsequent turns you can use your action to cast *earth tremor* around the totem again, if you don't, the totem dissipates.

#### Elemental Resistance Totem
*(totem of water)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down an elemental resistance totem, that casts the *absorb elements* spell on a target within 30 feet of it, the resistance lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Fire Nova Totem
*Prerequisite: 9th level, (totem of fire)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a fire nova totem, that casts the *fireball* spell. Once cast, the totem dissipates.

#### Flametongue Totem
*Prerequisite: 5th level, (totem of fire)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a flametongue totem, that casts the *aganazzar's scorcher* spell. On subsequent turns you can use your action to cast *aganazzar's scorcher* spell from the totem again, if you don't, the totem dissipates.

#### Grace of Air Totem
*(totem of air)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a grace of air totem, that casts the *fog cloud* spell, this spell does not require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Liquid Magma Totem
*Prerequisite: 5th level, (totem of fire)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a magma totem, that casts the *flaming sphere* spell, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Mana Spring Totem
*(totem of water)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a mana spring totem, that casts the *bless* spell, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Searing Totem
*(totem of fire)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a searing totem, that casts the *fire bolt* cantrip at the end of your turn. You can use your bonus action on subsequent turns to recast the *fire bolt* spell. The totem uses your shaman level to determine its damage.

#### Stone Bulwark Totem
*Prerequisite: 17th level, (totem of earth)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a stone bulwark totem, that casts the *wall of stone* spell, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Stoneskin Totem
*Prerequisite: 13th level, (totem of earth)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a stoneskin totem, that casts the *stoneskin* spell on a creature within 30 feet of it, this spell doesn't re-quire concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Stormlash Totem
*Prerequisite: 13th level, (totem of air)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a stormlash totem, that casts the *storm sphere* spell, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

#### Windfury Totem
*Prerequisite: 5th level, (totem of air)*
<div style='margin-top:-6px'></div>

You place down a windfury totem, that casts the *warding wind* spell on a creature within 15 feet of it, this spell doesn't require concentration, and lasts for the duration of the totem.

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/cPPYV7h.png' style='position:absolute; top:0px; right:0px; width:1200px' />
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/2eoJFGi.jpg' style='position:absolute; top:920px; right:0px; width:450px; mix-blend-mode:multiply;transform:scalex(-1)' />

