## Racial Feats
Races on Azeroth are not equal in strength, the average tauren is considerably stronger than the average human. This section introduces a collection of special feats that allow you to empower your character's race further. These feats are each associated with a race from earlier in this book, and summarized in the Racial Feats table. A racial feat represents either a deepening connection to your race's culture or a physical transformation that brings you closer to an aspect of your
race's lineage.

The cause of a particular transformation is up to you and your DM. A transformational feat can symbolize a latent quality that has emerged as you age, or a transformation might be the result of an event in the campaign, such as exposure to powerful magic or visiting a place of ancient significance to your race. 

##### Racial Feats
|&nbsp; Race                    | Feat                     |
|:------------------------------|:-------------------------|
|&nbsp; Dwarf (wildhammer)      | Spiritual Guidance       |
|&nbsp; Night Elf               | Darnassian Knowledge     |
|&nbsp; Orc                     | Spiritual Guidance       |
|&nbsp; Tauren                  | Spiritual Guidance       |
|&nbsp; Tauren                  | Tauren Endurance         |
|&nbsp; Troll                   | Spiritual Guidance       |
|&nbsp; Troll                   | Zandalari Fury           |
|&nbsp; Worgen                  | Hardened Predator        |
|&nbsp; Worgen                  | Neither Beast nor Man    |

### Darnassian Knowledge
*Prerequisite: Night elf*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

Your studies and training have given you a deeper under-standing of your kin, unlocking unique gifts. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Intelligence or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - You have advantage on stealth checks made in dim or unlit surroundings, and any ability checks made to notice you are made with disadvantage.
 - When you fail a death saving throw, you can call upon a wisp to guide your path, changing the failure to a success. Once done, the essence of the wisp continues to linger in you for two long rests, making you unable to call upon the aid of another.

### Hardened Predator
*Prerequisite: Worgen*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

You have become accustomed with your worgen worm, realizing some of the benefits that comes with the wolf-like shape. You gain the following benefits:
 - You have advantage on Wisdom (perception) checks that rely on hearing or smell.
 - Whilst your hands are empty, you can take the dash action as a bonus action, using all four limbs to run.
 - Your fur has grown longer and thicker, making you unaffected by the effects of extreme cold.
 - When you roll a Hit Die to regain hit points, you roll the Hit Die twice and use either roll.

<br>

### Neither Beast nor Man
*Prerequisite: Worgen*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

You have managed to control your worgen curse in a way most cannot, keeping it suppressed inside and regaining a glimpse of your former self. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - As part of a short or long rest, you can transform your-self into a human. While human, you appear as you did before getting affected by the curse. When subject to a saving throw to not go feral, you roll the dice twice with advantage, and use either roll. Making an attack roll whilst human stirs your blood, immediately trans-forming you back into a worgen.

### Spiritual Guidance
*Prerequisite: Dwarf (wildhammer), orc, tauren or troll*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

You've delved into the energy of spirits, the everlasting balance and harmony they bring to all life. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - You gain proficiency in either Nature or Survival.
 - You have advantage on saving throws against being frightened.
 - You learn the *healing spirit* spell and can cast it once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a short or long rest.

### Tauren Endurance
*Prerequisite: Tauren*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

You gain leather tough hide and improved recovery through hard training. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Strength, Dexterity or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - Your hide thickens. While you aren't wearing armor, you add your Constitution modifier to your AC. You can use a shield and still gain this benefit.
 - Your hit point maximum increases by an amount equal to your level when you gain this feat. Whenever you gain a level thereafter, your hit point maximum increases by an additional 1 hit point.

### Zandalari Fury
*Prerequisite: Troll*
<div style='margin-top:-7px;'></div>

The Zandalari trolls were able to channel their fury, a trait that has been passed down through ancient bloodlines to you. Making you a furious combatant for a short while.

As an action, you enter a berserk for a number of rounds equal to your Strength modifier (minimum of 1), granting you a second action on each of your turns. This action can't be used on spells or spell-like abilities. 

Once the berserk ends, you gain one level of exhaustion, and cannot use this ability again until you finish a long rest.

